Me a long time OFNer, but dont post too much.............and nobody misses me!
I have to admit, I'm a fair weather OFC'er.  Once fishing is over, I spend all of my time on the West Virginia football and basketball message boards.  Love it when i'm here though.

I have resorted to sitting on the side lines since I am working overseas and at times can not really post on active threads due to the fact of being out of range for some satellite internet connections etc.  Presently I am in Melbourne Australia and finishing up my work here and then heading on Monday to New Zealand for 3 weeks and then Singapore and then back home to Ontario by mid July for some bass fishing and back overseas by the first week of Sept.  The worst part is that I have been trying to get together with a couple of guys here to go out on the ocean fishing and things just have not been able to materialize as of yet so when it does happen I will post from somewhere out on the ocean between Australia and New Zealand.  Talk to everyone soon, and I will sit on the side and read the threads every so often.  Best regards, Sam

Hey Sam, really good to hear from you my friend, it's been a long time. I wondered where the heck you were but never thought you'd be on the other side of the world  It'd be good to have you posting here again, you always added alot to this board !!
Where is RichB and his great reports?    Who else is MIA on OFC ?
What about CCMT ?
What's his face....you know......darn, he likes to hunt and enjoys racing, is a Newfie, a grandpa, first name is Brian.  It just came to me....Misfish!  He taught me to look at men's shoes.

People come and go from these boards all the time for many different reasons and I couldn't even guess how many great members we've lost from OFC over the years.  Some leave quietly and just slip out the back door while others make a big deal of it and write long rambling good-byes.  Some come back after awhile and others are never heard from again.  Sad to see some leave and good to be rid of others.
How about Holdfast and Spike>  Haven't heard from him lately either?
